<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <%- include("../../parts/head") %>
</head>

<body class="d-flex flex-column min-vh-100 bg-wyrd-default">

    <!-- Navbar -->
    <%- include("../../parts/navbar") %>

        <!-- Content -->
        <div class="container min-vh-100 bg-light shadow-lg border-start border-end border-dark-subtle">
            <div class="container-content">
                <div class="row mb-3">
                    <div class="col">
                        <h3 class="lora-semibold">History</h3>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row gap-3">
                    <div class="col-md">
                        <p>
                            Aeld is an ancient world shaped by the rise and fall of civilizations over eons.
                            Though monsters, magic, and forgotten ruins exist, they are exceptions rather than the rule.
                            Most people spend their lives farming fertile valleys, working crowded cities, serving noble
                            houses, or traveling the trade roads that connect the world's great powers.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            For adventurers, Aeld is more than a backdrop. It is where reputations are
                            earned, alliances are forged, and fortunes are spent. Between adventures, its cities offer
                            opportunities to train, conduct research, pursue personal ambitions, and prepare for the
                            next journey.
                        </p>
                        <div class="row my-3">
                            <img class="img-fluid object-fit-cover" src="/img/history.png" />
                        </div>
                        <h6 class="lora-semibold">The Commonwealth</h6>
                        <p>
                            The Commonwealth encompasses the settled heart of Aeld, where kingdoms, city-states, and
                            free realms stand connected by ancient roads, thriving trade, and centuries of shared
                            history. While every nation governs itself, their borders are bound together by
                            diplomacy, commerce, and necessity. Merchants carry goods across the continent, pilgrims
                            journey between sacred sites, scholars exchange knowledge, and envoys work tirelessly to
                            preserve an often fragile peace.
                        </p>
                        <h6 class="lora-medium small">The Enclave</h6>
                        <p>
                            At the center of the Commonwealth lies the Enclave, the oldest and largest kingdom in the
                            realm. Its towering walls protect generations of history, wealth, and learning. Great
                            temples, universities, guild halls, and noble estates crowd its districts, while merchants
                            from every province fill its markets with goods from across the known world.
                        </p>
                        <h6 class="lora-medium small">The Noble Provinces</h6>
                        <p>
                            At the center of the Commonwealth lies the Enclave, the oldest and largest kingdom in the
                            realm. Its towering walls protect generations of history, wealth, and learning. Great
                            temples, universities, guild halls, and noble estates crowd its districts, while merchants
                            from every province fill its markets with goods from across the known world.
                        </p>
                        <h6 class="lora-medium small">The Heartlands</h6>
                        <p>
                            The Heartlands are a network of farming communities, mining towns, and local markets that
                            keep the realm supplied. Small villages and market towns are woven together by well-traveled
                            roads, rivers, and trade routes, ensuring food, timber, ore, and stone reach every corner of
                            the Commonwealth.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md">
                        <h6 class="lora-semibold">The Borderlands</h6>
                        <p>
                            The Borderlands stretch across the outer frontier of the Commonwealth, where civilization
                            steadily gives way to the untamed wilds beyond. Fortified towns, lonely keeps, and weathered
                            watchtowers stand
                            connected by roads that grow fewer and less certain the farther one travels.
                            Soldiers, wardens, trappers, hunters, and adventurers are common sights, for every journey
                            beyond the frontier carries the promise of discovery.
                        </p>
                        <h6 class="lora-semibold">The Highlands</h6>
                        <p>
                            Rugged mountains and windswept valleys define the Highlands, where hardy communities have
                            carved out lives amid stone, timber, and iron. Rich mineral deposits support mines,
                            foundries, and master smiths whose work is prized across the Commonwealth. The people of the
                            Highlands value independence, tradition, and kinship
                            above titles, and while they acknowledge the authority of the Crown, local customs often
                            carry equal weight.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

</body>

</html>